"'''Single Cell'''" is a 12-page comic story that appeared in [[Star Wars Tales 7|''Star Wars Tales'' 7]] and was collected in ''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 2]]''. The story was written by [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]], penciled by [[Jan Duursema]], inked by [[Ray Kryssing]], lettered by [[Steve Dutro]] and colored by [[David McCaig|Dave McCaig]]. It takes place six weeks before the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]] in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]].

==Plot summary==
Aboard the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] battleship ''[[Stockade]]'', the incarcerated [[Feeorin/Legends|Feeorin]] [[Nym/Legends|Nym]] recounts the story of how he got there to his [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidian]] cellmate.

In orbit around [[Maramere]] in the [[Havoc (starfighter)|''Havoc'']], Nym, [[Kole]] and [[Jinkins]] waited for the mercenary [[Vana Sage]] and her "buyers," a group of bounty hunters, to trade [[Scalphunter rifle|experimental weapons]] for [[Stygium/Legends|Stygium]] crystals.

Once on board the space station, Nym and his crew met the buyers to exchange goods. When Nym revealed that he had buried the [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]] for the weapons as a safeguard, a fight ensued between the crew of the ''Havoc'' and the bounty hunters.

Under the threat of [[Droideka/Legends|droidekas]], Sage captured the crew, sent Kole and Jinkins to Maramere in an escape pod, and took the ''Havoc'' as payment for delivering Nym to the Trade Federation.

Back in the cell, [[Jinkins|Merick]] and [[Kole|Bavo]] arrive to rescue Nym, who vows revenge on Vana Sage.

==Continuity==
The events of ''Single Cell'' have been brought into [[Star Wars Legends|Legends continuity]] via references in ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'' and ''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''.

